subSubSection.paragraph:
MALE (
paratype
: 
Figs. 1–6
; Table I). Similar to female in coloration, but with well-marked sexual dimorphism: 
1)
size slightly larger; 
2)
overall coloration paler and more sharply contrasting, especially much darker tergite stripes and distal portion of metasoma and telson; 
3)
pedipalps comparatively longer, more slender, and less strongly carinate, with manus elongate and fingers with tegument coriaceous; 
4)
mesosoma narrower and parallel-sided; 
5)
genital operculum with valves widely separated, with papillae present and conspicuously protruding; 
6)
pectines with teeth longer and stouter, and with basal middle lamella angulose-oval and less enlarged; 
7)
smooth patch of sternite V better defined and slightly bulky; 
9)
metasomal segments much longer and narrower.
